	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103599200452321><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=16506&mid=103599200452321>RE: Alla's Rating System</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=16506&mid=103599200452321#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=39893><span id=Scholar>Paghk</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>109 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Oct 30th 10:53 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>(NOTE: this post is only about the rating system used on the boards here - if you're looking for something else, just skip this post! Thanks! - P)<br><br>Actually, Janaleea, Allakhazam's uses a rating system that is strongly Post-based.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each post is able to be ranked by readers according to their whims, but in general utility and entertainment value are the most highly rewarded - the stuff you WANT to read when you come here.  Posts about your wang or &quot;monk item&quot; posts generally fall off the boards pretty fast, but there seem to be enough of them to maintain a presence (doh!).<br><br>Anywho: Each post is ranked by readers - a User's &quot;posting karma&quot; is the average of all their post's ranks.  So it's not how many posts you have that determines your status, or the size of your wang, as some people seem to think - but how useful what you has to say is, each and every time you post.  If someone consistently makes good posts, their overall karma will go up, and even an &quot;unranked&quot; post from them will have a good rating.  On the other hand, someone who continues to make awful posts will eventually be ranked so badly that most people will never have to see their blabbering.<br><br>You can also adjust your 'Karma Filter' to show you only posts within a certian range - so for searching for info on an obscure quest, you might want to include ALL posts, no matter how painful it may be.  If you just want to read complete sentances, set your rating a little higher, heh.  If you set your rating all the way up to 4.00 or more, you won't see a lot of content, but what you do should always be worth reading.<br><br>Anyway, I've babbled long enough, and while this is relevant to your one-sentance statement, I think I'm a bit long winded for the Beginners in Magic, hehe.    If you want to know more (which you probably don't, but...), click on the &quot;MAIN .. FAQ&quot; link at the top left.  ( <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/FAQ.html" target=_new>http://everquest.allakhazam.com/FAQ.html</a> ).<br><br>I hope I haven't bored anyone to tears here - I'll shut up so you can go back to camping Raster or the bear in Miragul's cave. <br>(Yikes!)<br><br>Paghk Heyokah'Zek<br>Dancing Bear of Morell-Thule<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=120263" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=120263</a><br><br>(EDIT: Addendum! - Dargadin - I wasn't just posting for you, but for everyone who reads on these boards.  It didn't seem (to me at least) that Janaleea knew exactly how the rating system worked (of course, they might not care that much, either, lol), and I know there are others out there that might want to know more.  Again, there is a link at the top of the page that has this (and a lot of other useful) info listed, but not everyone has the time to read everything.<br>  ... I thought your post was useful and rated it as such, too.  =)  Have a good day!<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Nov  4 20:58:44 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=120263 target=_new>- Paghk Heyokah'Zek, Morell-Thule</a></td></tr>
